<subSubSection pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1437,1192,1831]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1264,1291]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Description</emphasis>
. The NTM C5419 
<typeStatus box="[546,641,1264,1290]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">holotype</typeStatus>
is 
<quantity box="[673,739,1265,1291]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" unit="cm" value="11.0">11 cm</quantity>
high and 
<quantity box="[846,934,1264,1291]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" unit="cm" value="11.5">11.5 cm</quantity>
wide (
<figureCitation box="[1007,1103,1264,1291]" captionStart="FIGURE 60" captionStartId="78.[151,250,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure@78.[178,1409,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="78" captionText="FIGURE 60. Litophyton type specimens: a, L. carnatum n. sp., paratype NTM C3947; b, L. grandis n. sp., holotype NTM C5419, c-d. L. pandoraensis n. sp., c, holotype NTM C4053, d, paratype NTM C3945." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765049" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765049/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 60b</figureCitation>
). The stalk is 
<quantity box="[1252,1326,1264,1291]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" unit="cm" value="3.5">3.5 cm</quantity>
long. The polyps are up to 
<quantity box="[332,416,1301,1327]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="0.7">0.7 mm</quantity>
wide and 
<quantity box="[528,612,1300,1327]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.6 mm</quantity>
high, grouped in conical catkins.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1437,1192,1831]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,276,1337,1363]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Polyps</emphasis>
. With no arrangement of sclerites as points (
<figureCitation box="[775,872,1336,1363]" captionStart="FIGURE 61" captionStartId="79.[151,250,784,809]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,188,755]" captionTargetId="figure@79.[151,1436,181,759]" captionTargetPageId="79" captionText="FIGURE 61. Lateral views polyp armature of Litophyton species: a, L. carnatum n. sp., holotype NTM C4100; b, L. grandis n. sp., holotype NTM C5419, c, L. pandoraensis n. sp., holotype NTM C4053." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765051" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765051/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 61b</figureCitation>
). Abaxial and lateral sclerites are spindles unilaterally ornamented with many big spines, largest spindles present abaxially, up to 
<quantity box="[1021,1119,1373,1399]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.40 mm</quantity>
long, laterally they are up to 
<quantity box="[151,248,1409,1435]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.20 mm</quantity>
long (
<figureCitation box="[317,411,1408,1435]" captionStart="FIGURE 66" captionStartId="84.[151,248,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[190,1397,181,1884]" captionTargetId="figure@84.[190,1397,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="84" captionText="FIGURE 66. Litophyton grandis n. sp., holotype NTM C5419; a, abaxial and lateral point spindles; b, lateral point spindles; c, adaxial and tentacle scales; d, supporting bundle spindle, partly; e-f, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk; g-h, sclerites of surface layer base of stalk; i-j, spindles of interior base of stalk; k, tuberculation of interior base stalk spindle. Scale at a also applies to d, f, h, j; scale at b also applies to c; e, g." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765061/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 66a</figureCitation>
); laterally there also are some simple spindles (
<figureCitation box="[922,1014,1408,1435]" captionStart="FIGURE 66" captionStartId="84.[151,248,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[190,1397,181,1884]" captionTargetId="figure@84.[190,1397,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="84" captionText="FIGURE 66. Litophyton grandis n. sp., holotype NTM C5419; a, abaxial and lateral point spindles; b, lateral point spindles; c, adaxial and tentacle scales; d, supporting bundle spindle, partly; e-f, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk; g-h, sclerites of surface layer base of stalk; i-j, spindles of interior base of stalk; k, tuberculation of interior base stalk spindle. Scale at a also applies to d, f, h, j; scale at b also applies to c; e, g." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765061/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 66b</figureCitation>
).The adaxial sclerites are small curved scales, similar to those of the tentacles, up to 
<quantity box="[653,751,1444,1471]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="0.15">0.15 mm</quantity>
long (
<figureCitation box="[823,919,1444,1471]" captionStart="FIGURE 66" captionStartId="84.[151,248,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[190,1397,181,1884]" captionTargetId="figure@84.[190,1397,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="84" captionText="FIGURE 66. Litophyton grandis n. sp., holotype NTM C5419; a, abaxial and lateral point spindles; b, lateral point spindles; c, adaxial and tentacle scales; d, supporting bundle spindle, partly; e-f, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk; g-h, sclerites of surface layer base of stalk; i-j, spindles of interior base of stalk; k, tuberculation of interior base stalk spindle. Scale at a also applies to d, f, h, j; scale at b also applies to c; e, g." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765061/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 66c</figureCitation>
). Spindles of the supporting bundle are up to 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
long, with simple tubercles, and not projecting beyond the polyp (
<figureCitation box="[916,1012,1480,1507]" captionStart="FIGURE 66" captionStartId="84.[151,248,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[190,1397,181,1884]" captionTargetId="figure@84.[190,1397,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="84" captionText="FIGURE 66. Litophyton grandis n. sp., holotype NTM C5419; a, abaxial and lateral point spindles; b, lateral point spindles; c, adaxial and tentacle scales; d, supporting bundle spindle, partly; e-f, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk; g-h, sclerites of surface layer base of stalk; i-j, spindles of interior base of stalk; k, tuberculation of interior base stalk spindle. Scale at a also applies to d, f, h, j; scale at b also applies to c; e, g." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765061/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 66d</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1437,1192,1831]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,461,1516,1543]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Surface layer top stalk</emphasis>
. Mostly capstans and derivatives of capstans, 
<quantity box="[965,1119,1516,1543]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="0.125" valueMax="0.2" valueMin="0.05">0.05-0.20 mm</quantity>
long; a few spindles (not depicted) and unilaterally spinose spindles are also present, up to 
<quantity box="[842,926,1553,1579]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
long, with simple and complex tubercles (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 66" captionStartId="84.[151,248,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[190,1397,181,1884]" captionTargetId="figure@84.[190,1397,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="84" captionText="FIGURE 66. Litophyton grandis n. sp., holotype NTM C5419; a, abaxial and lateral point spindles; b, lateral point spindles; c, adaxial and tentacle scales; d, supporting bundle spindle, partly; e-f, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk; g-h, sclerites of surface layer base of stalk; i-j, spindles of interior base of stalk; k, tuberculation of interior base stalk spindle. Scale at a also applies to d, f, h, j; scale at b also applies to c; e, g." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765061/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 66</figureCitation>
e-f).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1437,1192,1831]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,472,1624,1651]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Surface layer base stalk</emphasis>
. Mostly capstans and derivatives of capstans (
<figureCitation box="[972,1050,1624,1651]" captionStart="FIGURE 66" captionStartId="84.[151,248,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[190,1397,181,1884]" captionTargetId="figure@84.[190,1397,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="84" captionText="FIGURE 66. Litophyton grandis n. sp., holotype NTM C5419; a, abaxial and lateral point spindles; b, lateral point spindles; c, adaxial and tentacle scales; d, supporting bundle spindle, partly; e-f, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk; g-h, sclerites of surface layer base of stalk; i-j, spindles of interior base of stalk; k, tuberculation of interior base stalk spindle. Scale at a also applies to d, f, h, j; scale at b also applies to c; e, g." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765061/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 66</figureCitation>
g-h), a few spindles and unilaterally spinose spindles are also present (not depicted). Capstans 
<quantity box="[793,948,1660,1687]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="0.125" valueMax="0.2" valueMin="0.05">0.05-0.20 mm</quantity>
long; spindles up to about 
<quantity box="[1248,1333,1661,1687]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.4 mm</quantity>
long. All sclerites with simple tubercles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1437,1192,1831]" box="[199,1373,1732,1759]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,354,1732,1759]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Interior stalk</emphasis>
. Spindles, up to 
<quantity box="[536,633,1732,1759]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="0.75">0.75 mm</quantity>
long, with pointed ends (
<figureCitation box="[909,987,1732,1759]" captionStart="FIGURE 66" captionStartId="84.[151,248,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[190,1397,181,1884]" captionTargetId="figure@84.[190,1397,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="84" captionText="FIGURE 66. Litophyton grandis n. sp., holotype NTM C5419; a, abaxial and lateral point spindles; b, lateral point spindles; c, adaxial and tentacle scales; d, supporting bundle spindle, partly; e-f, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk; g-h, sclerites of surface layer base of stalk; i-j, spindles of interior base of stalk; k, tuberculation of interior base stalk spindle. Scale at a also applies to d, f, h, j; scale at b also applies to c; e, g." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765061/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 66</figureCitation>
i-j) and simple tubercles (
<figureCitation box="[1265,1361,1732,1759]" captionStart="FIGURE 66" captionStartId="84.[151,248,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[190,1397,181,1884]" captionTargetId="figure@84.[190,1397,181,1884]" captionTargetPageId="84" captionText="FIGURE 66. Litophyton grandis n. sp., holotype NTM C5419; a, abaxial and lateral point spindles; b, lateral point spindles; c, adaxial and tentacle scales; d, supporting bundle spindle, partly; e-f, sclerites of surface layer top of stalk; g-h, sclerites of surface layer base of stalk; i-j, spindles of interior base of stalk; k, tuberculation of interior base stalk spindle. Scale at a also applies to d, f, h, j; scale at b also applies to c; e, g." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3765061" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3765061/files/figure.png" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Fig. 66k</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1360,1768,1795]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1437,1192,1831]" box="[199,1360,1768,1795]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,325,1769,1795]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Etymology</emphasis>
. The Latin grandis, great, large, grown, strong, refers to the strongly developed polyp sclerites.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
